;;; Commentary:[K
;;[K
;; Given 2 files as input, diff-actor generates the diff between them[K
;; and acts out the changes as live edits in an Emacs buffer.
;; The first file is used as the starting point and edits are made on
;; it to lead to the second file.
;; Has wrapper functions to pick up the 2 files from revision history
;; of various VCSs like git and p4.[K
;;[K
[K
;;; Installation:[K
;;[K
;; Install diff-actor.el in load-path
;; Basic file diff acting:[K
;;  (diff-actor file-name-1 file-name-2)[K
;; This function uses the Emacs variable diff-command for diff-ing
;;[K
;; VCS (vcs-name) wrappers:[K
;;  (diff-actor-vcs-name file-name &optional ver-1 ver-2)
;; This function uses the VCS specific diff command for diff-ing[K
;; ver1 and ver2 of file-name. Default values:
;;  ver1 - first version
;;  ver2 - top of tree[K
[K

;; P4 versions diff, requires p4[K
(defun diff-actor-p4-vers (&optional file-name ver-1 ver-2)[K
  (interactive)[K
  (if (file-executable-p p4-executable)[K
      (let ((diff-file (or file-name (read-file-name "Enter file name: ")))[K
            (diff-ver-1 (or ver-1 "1"))[K
            (diff-ver-2 (or ver-2 "head"))[K
            (tmp-file-1 (make-temp-file "diff-actor"))[K
            (tmp-file-2 (make-temp-file "diff-actor")))[K
        (setq diff-actor-real-file-name diff-file)[K
        (message "printing to %s, %s" tmp-file-1 tmp-file-2)[K
        (call-process p4-executable nil (list :file tmp-file-1)[K
                      nil "print" "-q" (concat diff-file "#" diff-ver-1))[K
        (call-process p4-executable nil (list :file tmp-file-2)[K
                      nil "print" "-q" (concat  diff-file "#" diff-ver-2))[K
        ;;(with-temp-file tmp-file-1[K

;;(with-temp-file tmp-file-2[K
        ;;  (p4-print (list (concat diff-file "#" diff-ver-2))))[K
        (diff-actor-file tmp-file-1 tmp-file-2))))[K
